                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                langAttribute="none"
                                text="&lt;p>In efforts to ensure that our Grants and Donations have a greater impact and directly benefit patients, we must be more focused and strategic in our review process. In 2026, AbbVie Australia and New Zealand &lt;b>will only&lt;/b> exclusively support initiatives that are aligned with AbbVie’s scientific focus areas and demonstrate a commitment to raising disease awareness, health equity, improving patient outcomes and access or advancing science and medical education.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>We only accept applications at set times each year.&amp;nbsp; Please submit your application by the closing dates below.&amp;nbsp; Late applications will not be considered.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;b>2026 Funding Application Closing Dates&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa; &lt;/b>Friday, 26th June&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Friday, 16th October&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>What are AbbVie’s scientific areas of interest?&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie’s scientific areas of interest include: rheumatology, dermatology, gastroenterology, hematology-oncology, solid tumors, urology, migraine, parkinson’s, spasticity and movement disorder, ophthalmology and hepatitis C.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
