                                    <item_1779906428914
                                        cq:panelTitle="Things to know before you apply"
                                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-27T14:28:45.383-04:00"
                                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                        sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                        langAttribute="none"
                                        text="&lt;p>Consider the following items when submitting your application:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Funding is only provided to not-for-profit or charity organisations or healthcare institutions (e.g. hospitals or medical entity);&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Your grant must be submitted at least 60 days prior to the decision requested by date;&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Your submission will be evaluated against predetermined criteria and must align with one of AbbVie’s scientific areas of interest (Rheumatology, Dermatology, Gastroenterology, Haematology-Oncology, Solid Tumors, Urology, Migraine, Parkinson’s, Spasticity and Movement Disorder, Ophthalmology and Virology);&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Your request must support one of the following:&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Disease awareness activities&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Health equity&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Improved patient outcomes and access&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Advances in science and medical education&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie won’t support requests for:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>An activity or event that doesn’t support medical or scientific knowledge to benefit Australian or the Australian healthcare community.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Entertainment, social activities, and sporting events.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Religious activities.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>From an individual (including HCPs).&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Activities/events that have already taken place.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Requests for operational costs, salaries, and equipment (that may be used for both personal and professional reasons (e.g., laptops, tablets, mobile phones, smart phones, iPad, and other similar items).&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Requests that do not include a budget breakdown.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Requests from start-ups or profit-making entities - all organisations must be not-for profit or charities.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>You will receive email notification from AbbVie if additional information is required.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>You will receive AbbVie’s decision via email. If approved, the authorised signer will receive required documentation (i.e. contractual agreement) electronically.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Grants must reconcile to the approved budget within 90 days following the grant end date.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                        textIsRich="true"/>
                                    <item_1779906441314
                                        cq:panelTitle="What’s the process?"
                                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-27T14:29:22.753-04:00"
                                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                        sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                        langAttribute="none"
                                        text="&lt;p>&lt;b>Step 1: Registration&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>All requests for funding must be submitted through our online form, and at least 60 days before the start date of an activity.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>You must:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Submit your application on behalf of the organisation using our online form.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Once you have completed the registration, you will receive an email confirmation.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>Step 2: Application review and payment&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie carefully considers every grant request. Criteria for awarding a grant includes but is not limited to:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Educational strategy&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Scientific and educational merit&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Target audience&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Geographic equity&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Availability of funds&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Adequate review time&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>We work to ensure that a decision will be made within four weeks of the application deadline. If you have questions, please contact hcofundingapplicationanz@abbvie.com. If an application is incomplete or funding type does not match the original request, a Request for Additional Information (RFAI) will be sent to the requestor.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>If your application is not successful, you will be sent an email notifying you of the outcome.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>If approved, you will be sent an email confirmation with instructions to review and electronically sign the contractual agreement.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>The contractual agreement must be signed by all parties, prior to the start date of the event to be considered a fully executed contract. Once signed you will receive an email requesting an invoice for payment.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>Step 3: Reconciliation and outcomes&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Reconciliation is required within 90 days after the completion of the program.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>For more information on applying for funding from AbbVie Australia download the AbbVie Funding Guide &lt;/b>&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.abbvie.com.au/content/dam/abbvie-com2/au/docs/abbVie-guide-to-funding-2024.pdf&quot;>&lt;b>here&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&lt;b>.&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                        textIsRich="true"/>
